title: For Sale:  American Browning A5 16 ga. & 100 rnds (factory)
postcontent:
This is a used browning A5 16 gauge semi-auto shotgun with a low early serial number. During WWII Browning had Remington make the A5 shotgun is St. Louis, MO due to the events taking place in Europe. This is a 16 gauge with 2-3/4" chamber. The barrel is 27.5" long. The choke is fixed. The gun is in very good original condition. The inside barrel and chamber are also in VG condition. This shotgun shipped out of the factory on August 24, 1942. There were appx. 45,000 made from 1940-1947. There was a differant engraving paturn on these models and the serial numbers are on the sides. This gun has light handeling marks by the butt (pictured). There are no cracks in the wood. This is a pretty un-common version of the A5 16 gauge to be in this nice a condition.

Included will be 100rnds of factory 16 ga. ammo- Factory ammo.

I will ship this firearm to an FFL Dealer or a Curios & Relics license only.
